  sodium: 890 mg
author: HelloFresh
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/cajun-spiced-pulled-pork-5a8f0d08ae08b52c697526c2
servings: 2
course: main course
time required: 20 minutes
cuisine: Cuban
---

Wash and dry all produce. Core, seed, and dice @green bell pepper{1%unit}(cored, seeded, and diced). Trim, then thinly slice @scallions{2%unit}(trimmed and thinly sliced), keeping greens and whites separate. Core, seed, and dice @tomato{1%unit}(cored, seeded, and diced). In a #small bowl{}, stir together @honey{1%ounce} and @hot sauce{1%teaspoon}.

Heat @butter{1%tablespoon} and @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #medium pan{} over medium-high heat. Break up @pulled pork{10%ounce} with your hands into shreds and add to pan. Stir in @Cajun spice blend{1%teaspoon} (we'll use more later) and a pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook, stirring a few times, until pork is warmed through and begins to brown, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Stir tomato, half the honey mixture, @chicken stock concentrate{1%unit}, and ½ cup @water{1/2%cup} into pan, followed by up to @Cajun spice blend{1%teaspoon} (to taste; save the last 1 tsp for the rice). Bring to a simmer and cook, stirring, until thick and saucy, ~{3-5%minutes}. Season with @salt and @pepper.

Meanwhile, heat @olive oil{1%tablespoon} in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat (use a #nonstick pan{} if you have one). Add bell pepper and cook until slightly softened, about ~{3%minutes}. Stir in scallion whites, remaining @Cajun spice blend{1%teaspoon}, and a large pinch of @salt{pinch}. Cook until fragrant, about ~{30%seconds}.

Add @microwaveable jasmine rice{8.5%ounce} and @butter{1%tablespoon} to pan with veggies, breaking up rice with a #spoon{}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until warmed through and starting to crisp, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Divide rice mixture between plates, then arrange pork on top. Drizzle with remaining honey mixture, if desired. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.